column1: Transmissivity and fluorescence are nominal and unedited except that some records were removed in editing temperature and salinity.
The Oxygen:Dissolved:CTD data in the CTD files should be considered:
± 0.8 ml/l from 75 to 300 dbar; data tend to be somewhat high in this high gradient region.
Data below 800 dbar tend to be low.
Data below 1200 dbar are considered unreliable by the manufacturer.
For details on the processing see processing report: 2007-13-proc.pdf
